DataElement.preferredName: Image Annotation Statement Subject Unique Identifier ISO21090.II.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A statement used to describe something found and to be addressed on an image or series of images. It describes a thing found, measured and graphically annotated on an image or images from the same series. It consists of a subject, predicate and object._Some matter, situation, or event that is thought about, written about, or discussed.:A set of characters used as a code that is unique in the context or the system for which it is created. It serves as a means of identification and reference (often instead of a name) for an entity, person, thing, function, procedure, activity, variable, or body of data._Identifier that uniquely identifies a thing or object.
